ed. While concepts key to some social activists, including gender mainstreaming, just transition, and climate justice are common terms, human rights and health remain "fringe issues" in climate change governance. The New Climate Activism explores why and how these activists brought their issues to climate change, and why some succeeded while others did not.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aEnvironmental justice. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aNGOs.  aParis Agreement.  aactivism.  aclimate change.  aclimate justice.  aenvironmental governance.  alabour movement.  awomen’s rights.40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753812540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487538125423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487538125/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles